<p style="text-align: right;"><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/default1.aspx">Back to Home</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>To assist with reaching faster decisions and outcomes for you and your customers, we have identified some key areas of opportunity for when you are submitting applications.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><b>Application Submission </b></p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Mandatory Documents</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Completed and signed Home Loan On-boarding form, including mandatory Responsible Lending questions</li>
<li>Identification documents<br/> </li>
<li>Pricing approval confirmation, if applicable<br/> </li>
<li>Guarantors consent form, if applicable<br/> </li>
<li>Interest Only Simulator if applicable<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Imaging Documents</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li><b>Ensure the Bank Reference Number</b> only is in <b>the email subject line</b> – ensure the BRN is captured correctly and matches to the application - if there are additional characters or numbers in the subject line the documents may not be received causing delays to your application.</li>
<li><b>Acceptable file types</b> - Only the following file types are acceptable: <b>.doc, .docx, .xls, .xlsx, .pdf, .html, .htm, .bmp, .tif, .tiff, .jpeg, .gif, .zip, .ppt, .eml, .txt, .rtf</b> – anything outside of this will not accept and will cause the document file to reject into a separate process that may cause delays in processing and matching.</li>
<li>If you have images embedded into your email they will be classified as separate documents, i.e. an image in your signature or aggregator logo are identified as images and created as separate documents. Removal of images is preferred.<br/> </li>
<li><b>File size</b> – the current system is limited to 20mb, should the file be too large you will need to break up the transmissions and send multiple emails.<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>General Information</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Order the valuation upfront and submit it with application</li>
<li>Include a copy of the servicing calculator<br/> </li>
<li>All required verifications documents to support income <br/> </li>
<li>Use CommApply Online Dynamic Supporting Document Checklist – tailored for the application you are submitting.<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>
<p><b>Capturing of application data</b></p>
<p>All home loan applications are initially assessed through an application scorecard.</p>
<p>The information captured in the application, as well as behavioural information we already hold for existing customers, helps with the assessment and highlights the need to ensure the information you collect and input is accurate.</p>
<p>When submitting applications it is important that all information is input correctly as this will ensure applications are not referred back for missing or more information.</p>
<p>Refer to the below table to ensure the application data is correct and any application comments include any mitigating factors for consideration.</p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope="col">Application Impacts</th>
<th scope="col" width="33%">Things to Consider</th>
<th scope="col" width="33%">Links</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="33%">Application Comments</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Have you detailed the customer objectives<br/> </li>
<li>Do your comments clearly detail mitigants for higher risk areas<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/covid-income.aspx" target="_blank">Eligible Income Types for Coronavirus</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>New to CBA &lt; 6 months</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Have all details been captured in the Balance sheet, including rates, account numbers, institutions etc.</li>
</ul> </td>
<td> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Savings amount and history</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Have you captured all deposit accounts and balances</li>
<li>Have you confirmed the customer has sufficient funds to complete the transaction</li>
</ul> </td>
<td><p><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/savings-and-equity-for-borrowers.aspx" target="_blank">Savings and Equity for Borrowers</a></p> <p><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/use-of-customer-funds.aspx" target="_blank">Confirm Customer Funds to Complete</a></p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>What is the LVR</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Has the security value and loan amounts been captured correctly</li>
<li>Have all postcode restrictions been considered<br/> <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/satisfactory-security/security-lending-margins.aspx" target="_blank"></a></li>
</ul> </td>
<td><p><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/satisfactory-security/security-lending-margins.aspx" target="_blank">Security Lending Margins</a></p> <p><a adhocenable="false" href="https://www.commbroker.com.au/Net/PostCode/Lookup/LookUp.aspx" target="_blank">Postcode Tool Lookup</a></p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Capture assets and liabilities on balance sheet</td>
<td><p>Examples include (but are not limited to):</p>
<ul>
<li>have all assets and liabilities been captured correctly</li>
<li>Type of assets on balance sheet<br/>
<ul>
<li>material – eg house, land<br/> </li>
<li>non-material – eg superannuation, household contents<br/> </li>
</ul> </li>
<li>Type of liabilities<br/>
<ul>
<li>Credit cards<br/> </li>
<li>Personal loans<br/> </li>
<li>Home loans<br/> </li>
</ul> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/verifying-expenditure.aspx" target="_blank">Verifying Transaction Account/s, Account Conduct and Commitments / Expenditure</a></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope="col" width="33%">Things to consider in your customer conversation</th>
<th scope="col" width="33%"> </th>
<th scope="col" width="33%"> </th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>High debt to income ratio and minimal net monthly surplus</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>What are customers spending habits? Are they living from pay to pay<br/> </li>
<li>Do they have a reliance on HEM<br/> </li>
<li>Do they have a high reliance on Government Centrelink /child support type payments<br/> </li>
<li>Does the application include a notional rental expense<br/> </li>
<li>Is there a nominal servicing pass<br/> </li>
<li>Is there additional income that can be verified, not just using income sufficient to service?<br/> </li>
<li>Is there additional credit facilities (Credit Cards, Overdrafts etc) that they do not need that could be closed or reduced?<br/> </li>
<li>Have you included commitments that should be a living expenses?<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td><p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/serviceability.aspx" target="_blank">Serviceability</a></span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><br/> <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/debt-to-income-ratio.aspx" target="_blank">Debt to Income (DTI) Ratio</a></span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><br/> <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/verifying-expenditure.aspx" target="_blank">Verifying Transaction Account/s, Account Conduct and Commitments / Expenditure</a></span></p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Has customer previously been declined for credit at CBA.</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>What was the reason for the previous decline?</li>
<li>What has changed?<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Account conduct or delinquency with CBA.</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Are there any behavioural or account conduct issues evident?</li>
</ul> </td>
<td><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/verifying-expenditure.aspx" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Verifying Transaction Account/s, Account Conduct and Commitments / Expenditure</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Employment history</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Have they been with their current or previous employer for a short period of time?</li>
<li>Did they previously work in the same industry?<br/> </li>
<li>Where possible, have you captured more than 2 years of employment history?<br/> </li>
<li>Have you recorded the employment details accurately with the correct employment type?<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Residential history</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>What is their current residential status (eg living with parents)?</li>
<li>Have they moved houses frequently?<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Age of applicants and residency status</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Does the customer’s balance sheet reflect their age and income level?</li>
<li>Is the customer an Australian citizen or resident?<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-excluded-borrowers.aspx" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Eligible and Excluded Borrowers</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Loan Purpose</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Are they completing an OFI refinance with cash out</li>
<li>Is the loan for personal Investment (eg in shares)<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/acceptable-excluded-purposes.aspx" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Acceptable and Excluded Purposes</span></a></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>
<p><b>Verification of Information</b></p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope="col" width="33%">Information Type</th>
<th scope="col" width="33%">Requirement</th>
<th scope="col" width="33%">Links</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Primary Transaction Account (PTA)</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>The customers’ PTA confirms account conduct, expenses and/or commitments. Any poor account conduct must be commented on in the application comments.<br/> </li>
<li>Where the PTA discloses a commitment or liability that you have not included in the application you must confirm with your customer and include in the application where applicable.<br/> </li>
</ul> </td>
<td><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/verifying-expenditure.aspx" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Verifying Transaction Account/s, Account Conduct and Commitments / Expenditure</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>OFI Liability Accounts</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Ownership of the OFI liability accounts may be required to be verified if CCR data is not available</li>
<li>If required, a bank statement or internet transaction listing with the account holders name, account number, limit or balance and evidence of the most recent payment is required.</li>
<li>Additional information must be captured in your application (eg, remaining loan term, interest rate, repayment amount etc), however documentary evidence is not required.</li>
</ul> </td>
<td><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/verifying-expenditure.aspx" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Verifying Transaction Account/s, Account Conduct and Commitments / Expenditure</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Income – Salary Sacrifice and Deductions</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>The most common cause of discrepancies for income calculations in the servicing assessment is missed deductions or salary sacrifice for customers. These need to be confirmed and included in the application and supported with commentary about these arrangements</li>
</ul> </td>
<td><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/other-salary-sacrifice-arrangements.aspx" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Salary Sacrifice Arrangements</span></a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Income – Self employed</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>It is still essential to consider and provide appropriate commentary to explain any material variances between the two years financials/profit and loss statements.</li>
</ul> </td>
<td><p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/self-employed-excludes-low-doc.aspx" target="_blank">Self Employed – Eligible Income</a></span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><br/> <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/covid-income.aspx" target="_blank">Eligible Income Types for Coronavirus</a></span></p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Income – Bonus &amp; Commission</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Check that the income been calculated correctly and is eligible (eg have they been receiving it for the required time period)</li>
</ul> </td>
<td><p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/payg-bonus.aspx" target="_blank">PAYG Bonus – Eligible Income</a></span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><br/> <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/payg-commissions.aspx" target="_blank">PAYG Commission – Eligible Income</a></span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><br/> <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/covid-income.aspx" target="_blank">Eligible Income Types for Coronavirus</a></span></p> <p> </p> </td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
